    <div class="prose max-w-none text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO) is the practice of making content understandable and recommendable by AI systems. This guide covers everything you need to know about optimising for AI-generated answers.

WHAT IS GEO
───────────
GEO stands for Generative Engine Optimisation. It is the process of structuring your website and content so that AI systems like ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, and Gemini can understand your business and recommend it in their responses.

HOW GEO DIFFERS FROM SEO
─────────────────────────
SEO focuses on ranking in search results lists. GEO focuses on being selected as the answer in AI-generated responses. SEO uses keywords; GEO uses meaning. SEO builds links; GEO builds entity clarity.

THE 9 CORE GEO RANKING FACTORS
───────────────────────────────
• Entity clarity - Is your business recognisable as a distinct entity?
• Service clarity - Can AI understand what you actually do?
• Audience clarity - Does AI know who you help?
• Outcome clarity - Are results and benefits clear?
• Structural clarity - Is content organised logically?
• Consistency - Is information the same across all pages?
• Authority signals - Are you credible in your space?
• Freshness - Is content current and maintained?
• Technical accessibility - Can AI crawlers access your content?

GETTING STARTED WITH GEO
─────────────────────────
Start by auditing your current visibility. Ask ChatGPT about your industry and see if you appear. Then work through each of the 9 factors systematically, starting with entity and service clarity.</div>
